TI  - Investment in new foreign subsidiaries under receding perception of uncertainty
JO  - Journal of International Business Studies
SP  - 370
EP  - 386
VL  - 39
IS  - 3
AB  - Research on foreign direct investment has focused considerable attention on the moment of market entry, but less on the dynamics of investment in the post-entry phase. This paper centres the influence of uncertainty on investment, and develops a growth options model to explain the sequence of investment in new foreign subsidiaries. In a learning process that starts at entry, investors perceive receding levels of uncertainty and shift their reason for investment from option values towards net present values. The findings of a panel study of 634 German subsidiaries support the propositions and reveal the potential of the real options approach to improve the understanding of internationalisation processes.
